feat: aggressive sparsity + adaptive per-layer k inference

Sparsity push:
- SPIKE_K: 5.0 -> 3.0 (40% more aggressive quantization grid)
- SPIKE_MAX: 31 -> 15 (tighter clamp = more compression)
- QAT k-curriculum: 50 -> 25 -> 12 -> 8 -> 5 now 50 -> 20 -> 10 -> 5 -> 3
- LoRA rank: 64 -> 128, alpha: 128 -> 256 (compensate for harder sparsity)
- QAT now supports both 4B and 9B models (was 9B-only)

Adaptive k:
- AdaptiveKController profiles per-layer activation distribution (variance,
  kurtosis) during first 10 forward passes, then locks optimal k per layer
- Low-variance layers get aggressive k (min 2.0), heavy-tail layers get
  conservative k (up to 8.0), typical layers use base k (3.0)
- Exposed in /health endpoint under spike_analysis.adaptive_k
